data.text:
Friday, February 10, 6 p.m. to 8 p.m.

Musical legend David Rovics performs live, in-person and virtually, songs from his recent album May Day that have the theme of solidarity among workers of the world.

The San Francisco Living Wage Coalition is supporting workers in Mexico who are organizing unions free of corporate influence.

The concert will be held at the historic Redstone Labor Temple located at 2940 â€“ 16th Street, a half block from the 16th Street BART station. It is wheelchair-accessible.

Tickets are $15 and can be purchased online here.

If you are unable or wish not to attend in-person, tickets include receiving a future link to view the event online.
